<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>RoosterLabs · You. AImplified.</title>
  <meta name="description" content="RoosterLabs guarantees your LinkedIn content cadence: we turn your real point of view into consistent posts — from the right topic to publishing. Built for senior professionals building authority.">
  <meta property="og:type" content="website">
  <meta property="og:locale" content="en_US">
  <meta property="og:title" content="RoosterLabs · You. AImplified.">
  <meta property="og:description" content="Knowing was never your problem. Turning it into content is.">
  <meta property="og:url" content="{{.BaseURL}}{{.PagePath}}">
  <meta property="og:image" content="{{.OGImageURL}}">
  <meta property="og:image:width" content="1200">
  <meta property="og:image:height" content="630">
  <meta property="og:image:type" content="image/png">
  <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
  <meta name="twitter:title" content="RoosterLabs · You. AImplified.">
  <meta name="twitter:description" content="Knowing was never your problem. Turning it into content is.">
  <meta name="twitter:image" content="{{.OGImageURL}}">
  <!-- Favicon = brand icon (Pedro's decision 2026-07-10, amendment to 003;
       replaces the provisional zigzag). Identity still calls for a solid
       micro version — swap here when it exists. -->
  <link rel="icon" href="/static/rooster-icon.png" type="image/png">
  <!-- Fonts via Google Fonts CDN (épico 002, T14): decorative, off the
       critical path — if it fails, the CSS fallback kicks in and the form
       keeps working. Different from htmx (vendored, see decisions.md),
       which is critical path. -->
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Albert+Sans:wght@300;400;500&family=Inter:wght@400;600&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/site.css">
  <!-- htmx vendored in /static: unpkg hung in production (2026-07-07). -->
  <script defer src="/static/htmx.min.js"></script>
  <script defer src="/static/app.js"></script>
</head>
<body data-language="{{.Lang}}" data-path="{{.PagePath}}" data-utm-source="{{.UTM.Source}}" data-utm-medium="{{.UTM.Medium}}" data-utm-campaign="{{.UTM.Campaign}}" data-utm-term="{{.UTM.Term}}" data-utm-content="{{.UTM.Content}}">
  <!-- Rooster watermark (v0.5, T8 amendment): full-page backdrop, large and
       centered, behind all content — decorative, hidden on mobile
       (visual-identity.md v0.5). Outside <header> on purpose: covers the page,
       not just the hero. -->
  <img class="site-watermark" src="/static/rooster-watermark.webp" alt="" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy">
  <header class="site-header">
    <a href="/" class="lang-link">Versão em português</a>
    <!-- v0.5: tagline promoted to H1, no eyebrow. Only the "AI" prefix gets
         amber — in Albert Sans the whole word in one color reads "Almplified"
         (capital I = lowercase l); see landing-page.md v0.5. -->
    <h1>You. <span class="ai-accent">AI</span>mplified.</h1>
    <p class="lead">RoosterLabs guarantees your LinkedIn content cadence: we turn your real point of view into consistent posts — from the right topic to publishing. Built for senior professionals building authority.</p>
    <p class="hero-close">The content is yours. The heavy lifting, ours.</p>
    <a class="hero-cta" href="#lead-form">Get an alpha seat</a>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="section">
      <h2>Knowing was never your problem.<br><span class="h2-accent">Turning it into content is.</span></h2>
      <p>Publishing consistently takes a system nobody told you about: spotting what in your day (and in the news) deserves your comment, finding <em>your</em> take on it, turning that into a post that sounds like you — and repeating it every week, with discipline, for months.</p>
      <p>You have the opinions and the experience. What you don't have is that system. Which is why almost everyone:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Posts on their own... for three weeks.</strong> Without a system, consistency dies in the first busy month.</li>
        <li><strong>Tries a generic AI tool.</strong> It writes — everyone's post, not yours.</li>
        <li><strong>Considers a ghostwriter.</strong> Solves the process at US$500–2,000+/mo, in someone else's voice.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>From trigger to published,<br><span class="h2-accent">with you at the center.</span></h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>We find the topic.</strong> From your field's news or your own editorial line — an idea bank that never runs dry. No more "what do I even post about?".</li>
        <li><strong>We listen to you.</strong> A quick conversation captures your actual take — the opinion, the experience, the lesson. Like a good interviewer, whenever it suits you.</li>
        <li><strong>We build the post around your view, in your voice.</strong> The AI does the heavy lifting of structuring and writing — from what you said, not from templates.</li>
        <li><strong>You approve and publish. Every week.</strong> Consistency stops depending on your discipline — that becomes our job. A rooster never forgets to crow.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="note">Transparency note: 100% software, from trigger to draft. No human ever writes for you — and the final word is always yours.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="compare-scroll">
        <table class="compare-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col"></th>
              <th scope="col">AI writing tools</th>
              <th scope="col">RoosterLabs</th>
              <th scope="col">Ghostwriters</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Writes the post</td><td><span class="mark-ok">✓</span></td><td><span class="mark-ok">✓</span></td><td><span class="mark-ok">✓</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td>From your real take, not a template</td><td><span class="mark-no">✗</span></td><td><span class="mark-ok">✓</span></td><td><span class="mark-ok">✓</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Triggers + an editorial line of your own</td><td><span class="mark-no">✗</span></td><td><span class="mark-ok">✓</span></td><td><span class="mark-ok">✓</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Consistency as part of the service</td><td><span class="mark-no">✗</span></td><td><span class="mark-ok">✓</span></td><td><span class="mark-ok">✓</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td>In your voice — not generic, not borrowed</td><td><span class="mark-no">✗</span></td><td><span class="mark-ok">✓</span></td><td><span class="mark-no">✗</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Software price</td><td><span class="mark-ok">✓</span></td><td><span class="mark-ok">✓</span></td><td><span class="mark-no">✗</span></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="note">Authenticity and effort have always been coupled: either you run the whole process, or you pay someone to fake being you. RoosterLabs decouples them.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section form-section">
      <h2>Alpha seats open — few, on purpose.</h2>
      <p>We're starting with a small group of alpha users: senior professionals building authority now, willing to shape the product with us. Beta seats come next; only then do we open up for real.</p>
      {{template "form_step_1_en" .}}
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <!-- Decorative icon (empty alt): the wordmark next to it already names
         the brand — alt="RoosterLabs" would double the screen-reader read. -->
    <p class="footer-brand">
      <img class="footer-icon" src="/static/rooster-icon.png" alt="" width="28" height="28">
      <span class="wordmark">Rooster<span class="wordmark-labs">Labs</span></span>
    </p>
    <p>RoosterLabs · contact: <a href="mailto:{{.ContactEmail}}">{{.ContactEmail}}</a> · <a href="/">Versão em português</a></p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
